WRITING.TITLE: Guys, what would you like for your birthday this year?

WRITING.TEXT: I too have a beagle who just had to get her toe cut off due to cancer. She's 11 but doesn't have too much longer left. Breaks my damn heart.

As a current dietetics student, it is a lot of work to become a registered dietitian. 4 years undergrad with similar sciences to premed, a year long (rarely paid) internship, and within the next couple years a masters will be required.
